Overview:
An API security assessment was conducted against the University Vuln application to identify security weaknesses affecting confidentiality, integrity, and availability.
The assessment focused on authentication mechanisms, authorization controls, object-level access control, input handling, rate-limiting implementation, and exposure of sensitive information.
Multiple vulnerabilities were identified, including Broken Object Level Authorization (BOLA), Insecure Direct Object Reference (IDOR), Mass Assignment, Sensitive Data Exposure, and Missing Rate Limiting Controls.

