Finding 1: Broken Object Level Authorization (BOLA)
Severity: Critical

Endpoint
/grads

Description:
The API failed to validate ownership and authorization checks when accessing grade-related resources.
An authenticated user was able to access objects belonging to other users by modifying object identifiers.

Impact:
An attacker may:
Access grades of other students
Retrieve academic information
Violate student privacy
Enumerate records
OWASP Mapping

OWASP API1:2023 Broken Object Level Authorization

Recommendation
Enforce authorization checks on every object request
Validate ownership server-side
Implement role-based access controls

Finding 2: Insecure Direct Object Reference (IDOR)
Severity: High

Endpoint
/students
Description:
The application exposed direct references to student resources without sufficient authorization validation.
Manipulating identifiers allowed unauthorized access to records belonging to other users.

Impact

Potential exposure of:
Student information
Academic records
Personal identifiers

Recommendation:
Replace predictable identifiers
Enforce object-level authorization
Use indirect references where applicable

Finding 3: Mass Assignment
Severity: Critical

Endpoint
/login
Modified Parameter
{
  "isAdmin": true
}
Description:
The API accepted user-supplied parameters without properly restricting assignable attributes.
The tester was able to submit administrative fields not intended for user control.

Impact:

Potential consequences include:
Privilege escalation
Unauthorized administrative access
Full application compromise
OWASP Mapping

OWASP API6:2023 Unrestricted Access to Sensitive Business Flows

Recommendation
Use allowlists for accepted parameters
Reject unexpected attributes
Implement server-side role enforcement

Finding 4: Sensitive Data Exposure
Severity: High

Description:
The API disclosed sensitive information through responses.
Exposed Data
Student IDs
Password hashes

Impact:
Exposure of password hashes may facilitate:
Offline cracking attempts
Credential attacks
User enumeration

Recommendation:
Remove sensitive information from API responses
Minimize exposed fields
Implement data classification policies

Finding 5: Missing Rate Limiting
Severity: Medium

Endpoint
/fee
Requests Sent
70 Requests
Description:
The endpoint did not enforce sufficient rate limiting controls.
Multiple requests were processed without restrictions.

Impact

Potential abuse includes:

Brute-force attacks
Resource exhaustion
API abuse
Automated scraping

Recommendation:
Implement rate limiting
Introduce throttling mechanisms
Monitor excessive requests
Apply account/IP-based restrictions

