Conclusion:
The assessment identified multiple authorization and access control weaknesses affecting the API.
The most critical issues involve Broken Object Level Authorization and Mass Assignment vulnerabilities, both of which may allow unauthorized access to sensitive information and privilege escalation.
Immediate remediation should prioritize:

Authorization Enforcement
Object-Level Access Control
Parameter Validation
Sensitive Data Protection
Rate Limiting Controls

Addressing these findings will significantly improve the security posture of the University Vuln application and reduce the risk of unauthorized access, data exposure, and privilege escalation.
